{"tid":1702313,"cid":19,"subCid":0,"title":"讀科大嘅入嚟","createTime":"2019-11-09T15:26:02.000Z","updateTime":"2019-11-10T04:56:03.000Z","uid":4238,"like":62,"dislike":1,"uniUserReply":54,"replies":[{"pid":"1b4d7263b65fd3a683ffc5ce383275acefa9384d","tid":1702313,"uid":4238,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-11-09T15:26:02.000Z","msg":"<span style=\"color: red;\"><span style=\"font-size: x-large;\">學校話星期一（11/11）停課啊，畀哂機會大家去三罷！<br />\n</span></span><br />\n<br />\n<br />\nDear staff and students,<br />\n<br />\nTo allow sufficient time to repair the damage caused to the campus on Friday, the University <span style=\"color: red;\">has decided to cancel all classes and official events on Monday 11th November</span>. All University offices, Library and indoor sports facilities will be closed. Outdoor sports facilities including the tennis courts, seafront outdoor basketball court and the mini soccer pitch will remain open. As for the retail outlets and on-campus catering services, Campus Services Office (CSO) will keep you posted on their opening hours via email. <br />\n<br />\nThe Program Directors/Course Instructors will be in touch with the students shortly on the make-up sessions for the classes cancelled these few days. Should you have any difficulties, please discuss with your Program Director, UG Coordinator, or Course Instructor. <br />\n<br />\nThe University will issue further updates in due course.<br />\n<br />\nRegards,<br />\n<br />\nOffice of the Provost <br />\nOffice of the Vice-President for Administration and Business​"},{"pid":"19243dd1f6f31c232cc81f3c3a8013f54f8dca13","tid":1702313,"uid":4238,"like":3,"dislike":0,"score":3,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-11-09T15:27:43.000Z","msg":"推<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/kill.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> 唔好再話上堂不了，畀哂成日你罷喇<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/kill2.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"4099636e781d1e5e9ac816b1c8186ee811a09b33","tid":1702313,"uid":10135,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0